## Cycle 3 objective
Build `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`: assemble per-match, FOOTBALL-ONLY covariate vectors for both historical training matches (from martj42) and current WC2026 state (from the live adapter). Covariates required:
- Elo and Elo-difference (CONSUME from `data/elo.py` — do NOT recompute)
- Dixon-Coles attack/defence abilities (CONSUME from `simulation/poisson.py` — do NOT refit)
- FIFA ranking, with confederation as fallback when ranking is stale/unavailable
- time-weighted recent form
- goal difference
- rest days
- confederation (UEFA/CONMEBOL/CAF/AFC/CONCACAF/OFC) — static map needed; cnc8 FIFA-ranking data ends 2020-12-10
- neutral-venue flag

## Hard constraints (locked decisions)
- Football-only: NO socio-economic / market-value / GDP / yfinance features. NO bookmaker odds (odds are a Cycle-5 backtest baseline only).
- Do NOT compute Elo or Dixon-Coles abilities (that's Cycle 2, already done — consume their outputs).
- Do NOT train any model or define `[rf]` hyperparameters (Cycle 4). Do NOT run Monte Carlo / backtests (Cycle 5).
- Time-aware construction: NO forward leakage — a match's features must use only information available strictly before that match (recent form, rest days, Elo all pre-match). Deterministic given a seed.
- Must run no-key (martj42 + computed Elo/Poisson + static confederation map); live WC2026 state is optional and key-gated.
- Feature frames must cover BOTH historical training matches AND current WC2026 matches.
- New module ships with tests; the existing ~248-test suite (actually ~497 test funcs) stays green.

## Existing building blocks (already merged on main — consume, don't rebuild)
- `data/martj42_loader.py` — `Martj42Loader.load_results()` → DataFrame cols `DATE` (object ISO string), `HOME_TEAM`, `AWAY_TEAM` (crosswalk-normalized), `HOME_GOALS`/`AWAY_GOALS` (nullable Int64, <NA> for unplayed incl. WC2026), `TOURNAMENT` (object), `NEUTRAL` (bool). `wc2026_schedule(df)` filters WC fixtures.
- `data/elo.py` — `EloEngine.run(df) -> EloResult` with `.match_diffs` (list[MatchEloDiff: date, home_team, away_team, home_elo, away_elo, elo_diff, neutral], 1:1 with sorted input rows), `.history` (list[EloRating: team, date, rating]), `.final_ratings` (dict), `seed_wc2026(result, teams)`. `compute_elo(df, config)` factory.
- `simulation/poisson.py` — `fit_dixon_coles(df, config) -> TeamAbilities(attack: dict, defence: dict, home_adv, rho, intercept)`. `lambdas(abilities, home, away, neutral)`.
- `data/live.py` — `TournamentState(played, remaining_group_fixtures, standings)`, `LiveMatch`, `GroupStanding`, `TableRow`. `fetch_tournament_state(client, competition)`.
- `data/crosswalk.py` — `normalize_team`, `normalize_series`.
- `config.py` — Pydantic config sections (`EloConfig`, `PoissonConfig`, `Martj42Config`), `AppConfig` composition, `@field_validator`. There is NO confederation map or FIFA-ranking loader yet.

## Conventions to enforce
SOLID, SRP, TDD, KISS, YAGNI, vertical slices. Methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines. `from __future__ import annotations`; frozen dataclasses for value objects; Pydantic config with `ConfigDict(extra="ignore")`; module-level factory functions wrapping classes; DI (config passed in, no globals); `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`; `|` unions not Optional; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100. Tests: BDD `test_when_..._then_...`, in-memory DataFrames, no network/IO.

## Deliverable
A phased, dependency-ordered decomposition of Cycle 3 into 3-6 INDEPENDENT, single-session, testable tasks (vertical slices). For EACH task specify:
- Title (imperative "feat: ..." style)
- Goal (what + why)
- Files to CREATE (full paths) and MODIFY (path + what changes)
- Key data flows / function signatures (e.g. how the builder looks up pre-match Elo per row without leakage; how confederation fallback degrades; how rest-days and recent-form are computed time-aware)
- Acceptance criteria (testable)
- Dependencies on other Cycle-3 tasks
- Which stack/layer (all Python/data/features here)

Think hard about: (a) the cleanest decomposition — e.g. static confederation map + FIFA-ranking handling as one slice, the core per-match feature assembler as another, time-aware form/rest-days helpers, the live-WC2026 feature frame as a slice, and a config+exports slice; (b) how to guarantee NO forward leakage in the join between match rows and Elo/form/rest-days; (c) where a `FittedDistribution`-style frozen feature-row dataclass or a tidy DataFrame output belongs; (d) the public API/exports a new `features/__init__.py` should expose. Return the plan as structured markdown.
