All five issues are live on the `Cycle 3 — Football-Only Covariates` milestone, correctly labeled and dependency-ordered.

## Summary

**Cycle 3 — Feature Assembly** decomposed into 5 independent, dependency-ordered, single-session vertical slices. All tasks are pure Python feature engineering, so the support agent is `python-pro` + `python-expert` skill throughout (matrix "Generic Python" row).

```
Issue #7:  feat: static confederation map + FIFA-ranking fallback resolver + [features_build] config   [agent: python-pro]  priority:high
Issue #8:  feat: time-aware recent-form, rest-days, and goal-difference helpers (no forward leakage)    [agent: python-pro]  priority:high
Issue #9:  feat: core per-match feature assembler over martj42 history (features/build.py)              [agent: python-pro]  priority:high
Issue #10: feat: WC2026 current-state feature frame (no-key martj42 schedule + key-gated live adapter)  [agent: python-pro]  priority:medium
Issue #11: feat: features package public API, exports, and no-key integration smoke test                [agent: python-pro]  priority:medium
```

**Dependency graph:** `#7 → #8 → #9 → #10 → #11` (#9 needs #7+#8; #10 needs #7+#9; #11 needs all).

**Key architectural decisions encoded in the issues** (from the `Explore` + `Plan` planning passes):
- **No-leakage invariant:** the builder anchors to one chronological sort byte-identical to the Elo engine's, so `EloResult.match_diffs[i]` aligns positionally with `sorted_df.iloc[i]`; a per-row alignment guard raises `ValueError` on drift rather than silently leaking. All time-aware helpers read only `index < before_idx`.
- **Consume, don't recompute:** Elo (`compute_elo`) and Dixon-Coles (`fit_dixon_coles`) are computed once and injected (DI) into `build()` — shared between historical and WC2026 frames.
- **Football-only enforcement:** an explicit output-column allow-list test guarantees no socio-economic/market-value/GDP/odds fields. Confederation comes from a new static `CONFEDERATION_MAP`; ranking degrades to confederation when stale (cnc8 ends 2020-12-10) or absent.
